Class DynamicListView

    Drawable.Callback, NoCopySpan, TextWatcher, AccessibilityEventSource, KeyEvent.Callback, ViewManager, ViewParent, ViewTreeObserver.OnGlobalLayoutListener, ViewTreeObserver.OnTouchModeChangeListener, Filter.FilterListener

    public class DynamicListView
extends ListView
    A ListView implementation which provides the following functionality:
    • Drag and drop
    • Swipe to dismiss
    • Swipe to dismiss with contextual undo
    • Animate addition

        NOTE: This method can only be called on devices running ICS (14) and above, otherwise an exception will be thrown.

      • enableSimpleSwipeUndo

        public void enableSimpleSwipeUndo()
        Enables swipe to dismiss with contextual undo for this DynamicListView. This method requires that a SwipeUndoAdapter has been set. It is allowed to have the SwipeUndoAdapter wrapped in a BaseAdapterDecorator.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the adapter that was set does not extend SwipeUndoAdapter.

      • disableSwipeToDismiss

        public void disableSwipeToDismiss()
        Disables any swipe to dismiss functionality set by either enableSwipeToDismiss(com.nhaarman.listviewanimations.itemmanipulation.swipedismiss.OnDismissCallback), enableSwipeUndo(com.nhaarman.listviewanimations.itemmanipulation.swipedismiss.undo.UndoCallback) or enableSimpleSwipeUndo().

      • setAdapter

        public void setAdapter(ListAdapter adapter)
        Sets the ListAdapter for this DynamicListView. If the drag and drop functionality is or will be enabled, the adapter should have stable ids, and should implement Swappable.
        Overrides:
        setAdapter in class ListView
        Parameters:
        adapter - the adapter.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the drag and drop functionality is enabled and the adapter does not have stable ids.
        IllegalArgumentException - if the drag and drop functionality is enabled and the adapter does not implement Swappable.

      • insert

        public void insert(int index,
          Object item)
        Inserts an item at given index. Will show an entrance animation for the new item if the newly added item is visible. Will also call Insertable.add(int, Object) of the root BaseAdapter.
        Parameters:
        index - the index the new item should be inserted at.
        item - the item to insert.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the adapter that was set does not implement Insertable.

        public <T> void insert(Pair<Integer,T>... indexItemPairs)
        Inserts items at given indexes. Will show an entrance animation for the new items if the newly added item is visible. Will also call Insertable.add(int, Object) of the root BaseAdapter.
        Parameters:
        indexItemPairs - the index-item pairs to insert. The first argument of the Pair is the index, the second argument is the item.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the adapter that was set does not implement Insertable.

      • insert

      • setDraggableManager

        public void setDraggableManager(DraggableManager draggableManager)
        Sets the DraggableManager to be used for determining whether an item should be dragged when the user issues a down MotionEvent.

        This method does nothing if the drag and drop functionality is not enabled.

      • setOnItemMovedListener

        public void setOnItemMovedListener(OnItemMovedListener onItemMovedListener)
        Sets the OnItemMovedListener that is notified when user has dropped a dragging item.

        This method does nothing if the drag and drop functionality is not enabled.

      • startDragging

        public void startDragging(int position)
        Starts dragging the item at given position. User must be touching this DynamicListView.

        This method does nothing if the drag and drop functionality is not enabled.

        Parameters:
        position - the position of the item in the adapter to start dragging. Be sure to subtract any header views.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the user is not touching this DynamicListView, or if there is no adapter set.

      • setScrollSpeed

        public void setScrollSpeed(float speed)
        Sets the scroll speed when dragging an item. Defaults to 1.0f.

        This method does nothing if the drag and drop functionality is not enabled.

        Parameters:
        speed - <1.0f to slow down scrolling, >1.0f to speed up scrolling.

      • setDismissableManager

        public void setDismissableManager(DismissableManager dismissableManager)
        Sets the DismissableManager to specify which views can or cannot be swiped.

        This method does nothing if no swipe functionality is enabled.

        Parameters:
        dismissableManager - null for no restrictions.

      • fling

        public void fling(int position)
        Flings the View corresponding to given position out of sight. Calling this method has the same effect as manually swiping an item off the screen.

        This method does nothing if no swipe functionality is enabled.

        Parameters:
        position - the position of the item in the ListAdapter. Must be visible.

      • setSwipeTouchChild

        public void setSwipeTouchChild(int childResId)
        Sets the resource id of a child view that should be touched to engage swipe. When the user touches a region outside of that view, no swiping will occur.

        This method does nothing if no swipe functionality is enabled.

        Parameters:
        childResId - The resource id of the list items' child that the user should touch to be able to swipe the list items.

      • setMinimumAlpha

        public void setMinimumAlpha(float minimumAlpha)
        Sets the minimum value of the alpha property swiping Views should have.

        This method does nothing if no swipe functionality is enabled.

        Parameters:
        minimumAlpha - the alpha value between 0.0f and 1.0f.

      • dismiss

        public void dismiss(int position)
        Dismisses the View corresponding to given position. Calling this method has the same effect as manually swiping an item off the screen.

        This method does nothing if no swipe functionality is enabled. It will however throw an exception if an incompatible swipe functionality is enabled.

        Parameters:
        position - the position of the item in the ListAdapter. Must be visible.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the SwipeTouchListener that is enabled does not extend SwipeDismissTouchListener.

      • undo

        public void undo(View view)
        Performs the undo animation and restores the original state for given View.

        This method does nothing if no swipe functionality is enabled. It will however throw an exception if an incompatible swipe functionality is enabled.

        Parameters:
        view - the parent View which contains both primary and undo Views.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the SwipeTouchListener that is enabled doe snot extend SwipeUndoTouchListener.
